1931;;A Holy Terror;;American;;Irving Cummings;;George O'Brien, Sally Eilers, Humphrey Bogart;;western;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Holy_Terror;;Polo player Tony Bard (George O'Brien) travels West to investigate his father's murder, and meets Jerry Foster (Sally Eilers) on a Wyoming ranch. After being kidnapped, Tony escapes and discovers his true father (James Kirkwood) and learns that he was raised by another man (Robert Warwick) who was in love with his mother.[1][2]